94.6	Oulipo	Oulipo	Oulipo is a loose gathering of (mainly) French-speaking writers and mathematicians which seeks to create works using constrained writing techniques. It was founded in 1960 by Raymond Queneau and Fran√ßois Le Lionnais. Other notable members have included novelists Georges Perec and Italo Calvino, poets Oskar Pastior Jean Lescure and poet/mathematician Jacques Roubaud.	
